To brew a proper cup of Tristan rock tea using our island method, here be the steps ye follow:

```
<?tristan
$kettle = "big iron pot";
$water = "fresh spring water";
$tea_leaves = "hand-picked island tea";
$brew_time = "five good minutes";

// Set the pot on the fire
$kettle->fill($water);
$kettle->heat("until bubbles dance proper");

// Steep the leaves
$mug = new Mug();
$mug->add($tea_leaves);
$mug->pour($kettle->water);
$mug->wait($brew_time);

// Enjoy
if ($mug->taste == "strong and sweet") {
    echo "Tea be ready, me old china!";
} else {
    echo "Let it steep a wee bit longer...";
}
?>
```
